{"article_id":"23JQ4hyrHr35ZcJt","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"LONDON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Theresa May ended her failed three-year quest","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"to lead Britain out of the European Union","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"on Friday ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"announcing","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"that she will step down as Conservative Party leader June 7","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"and triggering a contest","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"to choose a new prime minister","depth":12},{"id":8,"text":"who will try to complete Brexit .","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"\" I have done my best , \"","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"May said in a speech outside 10 Downing St. ,","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"as close aides and her husband Philip looked on ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"before acknowledging","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that it was not good enough .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"Concluding her remarks ,","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"she struggled to contain her emotions","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"and her voice broke","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"as she expressed","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"\" enduring gratitude","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"to have had the opportunity","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"to serve the country","depth":14},{"id":21,"text":"I love . \"","depth":14},{"id":22,"text":"Then she turned","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"and strode through the famous black door of No . 10 .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"May will stay on as a caretaker prime minister","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"until the new leader is chosen , a process","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"the Conservatives aim to complete by late July .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"The new party leader will become prime minister","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"without the need for a general election .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"She became prime minister","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"the month","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"after the U.K. voted in June 2016 to leave the European Union ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"and her premiership has been consumed by the attempt","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"to deliver on that verdict .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"May was brought down by Brexit ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"but her nemesis wasn ' t the EU ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"with which she successfully struck a divorce deal .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"She was felled by her own Conservative Party ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"which refused to accept it .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"The plan was defeated three times in Parliament ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"rejected both by pro-EU opposition lawmakers and by Brexit-supporting Conservatives","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"who thought","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"it kept Britain too closely bound to the bloc .","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"Many Conservative lawmakers came to see May as an obstacle","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"and blamed her for the U.K. ' s failure to leave the EU on the scheduled date of March 29 .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"The bloc has extended that deadline until Oct. 31 in hope","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Britain ' s politicians can break their political deadlock .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"The pressure on May reached breaking point this week","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"as House of Commons Leader Andrea Leadsom quit","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"and several Cabinet colleagues rejected the bill","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"she planned to put before Parliament","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"in a fourth attempt","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"to secure lawmakers ' backing for her Brexit blueprint .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"In her farewell speech , May defended her record ,","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"she had \" negotiated the terms of our exit and a new relationship with our closest neighbors","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"that protects jobs , our security and our Union . \"","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"\" I have done everything","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"I can","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"to convince MPs to back that deal , \"","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"\" Sadly , I have not been able to do so . \"","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"\" It is now clear to me","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that it is in the best interests of the country for a new prime minister","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"to lead that effort , \"","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"she added .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Multiple contenders are already jockeying","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"to replace her in a contest","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"that will see a new leader","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"chosen by Conservative lawmakers and party members .","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"The early front-runner is Boris Johnson , a former foreign secretary and strong champion of Brexit .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"Other contenders are likely to include Leadsom , Foreign Secretary Jeremy Hunt and former Brexit Secretary Dominic Raab .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Johnson ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"whose relentless criticism helped push May out of the door ,","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"tweeted :","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"\" Thank you for your stoical service to our country and the Conservative Party .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"It is now time","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"to follow her urgings :","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"to come together","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"and deliver Brexit . \"","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Whether it is Johnson or another contender ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"the next prime minister is likely to be a staunch Brexiteer ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"who will try to renegotiate the divorce deal ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"and","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"if that fails ,","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"to leave the bloc without an agreement on the terms of the departure .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"\" The person","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"who will replace her","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"will embrace the possibility of a no deal with alacrity rather than fear , \"","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"said Steven Fielding , professor of political history at the University of Nottingham .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"\" They will have to embrace it","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"if they want to be elected by the Tory party membership . \"","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"Most businesses and economists think","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"that would cause economic turmoil","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"and plunge Britain into recession .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"Parliament has voted to rule out a no-deal Brexit ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"though it remains the legal default option .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"But many Conservatives think","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"embracing a no-deal Brexit may be the only way","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to keep the support of voters","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"who opted in 2016 to leave the EU .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"The Conservatives expect to take a bruising","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"when results come in late Sunday from this week ' s European Parliament election ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"which many British voters are expected to use","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"to express displeasure over the political gridlock .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Opinion polls suggest","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Conservative voters deserting in droves to the single-issue Brexit Party","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"led by Nigel Farage .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"Any attempt","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"to take Britain out of the EU","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"without a deal","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"will be fiercely resisted by Parliament ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"and could see pro-Europeans leave the Conservative Party .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon , an opponent of Brexit , tweeted","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"that May ' s exit \" will not solve the Brexit mess","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"that the Tories have created .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"... The prospect of an even more hard-line Brexiteer now becoming PM","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"and threatening a no deal exit","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"is deeply concerning . \"","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"EU leaders expressed respect for May ,","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"and stressed","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"they would not renegotiate the Brexit deal .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"\" We have set out our position on the withdrawal agreement and on the political declaration , \"","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"said EU spokeswoman Mina Andreeva .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"She said","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"European Commission President Jean-Claude Juncker had great respect for May","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"and would \" equally respect and establish working relations \" with any new British leader .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"German Chancellor Angela Merkel said","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"Germany would continue to \" do everything","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"it can","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"to ensure","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"there is a good partnership with Britain , an orderly exit ,","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"and then continuing good cooperation . \"","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"U.S. President Donald Trump ,","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"who has sometimes differed publicly with May ,","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"he was \" feeling badly \" for her .","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"\" I like her very much , \"","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"said Trump","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"who is due to meet May on a state visit to Britain June 3-5 .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"\" To succeed ,","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"he or she will have to find consensus in Parliament","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"where I have not , \"","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"\" Such a consensus can only be reached","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"if those on all sides of the debate are willing to compromise . \"","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"She said","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"it had been \" the honor of my life \" to serve as Britain ' s leader , the second woman","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"to hold the job ,","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"after Margaret Thatcher .","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"\" The second female prime minister","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"- but certainly not the last , \"","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"May said .","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"- Associated Press writers Gregory Katz in London , Raf Casert in Brussels and David Rising in Berlin contributed .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":307,"left":0,"right":306,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":306,"left":305,"right":153,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":305,"left":218,"right":304,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":199,"right":217,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":199,"left":181,"right":198,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":176,"right":180,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":176,"left":161,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":156,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":155,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":4,"right":159,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":159,"left":5,"right":158,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":6,"right":157,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":165,"right":174,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"paren